## FR-3: Admin Functional Requirements

### FR3.1 – Admin Login
The system shall authenticate administrators with full privileges.

### FR3.2 – View All Users (UI + API)
Admins shall view all registered users, including account status and roles.
The system shall also expose this information via an API endpoint.

### FR3.3 – Activate / Deactivate Accounts (UI + API)
Admins shall enable or disable accounts through UI and through secure API calls.

### FR3.4 – Reset User Passwords (UI + API)
Admins shall trigger password resets, including via a protected Admin API endpoint.

### FR3.5 – Manage System Roles (UI + API)
Admins shall assign or modify user roles (User/Coach/Admin).
A role management API endpoint shall be available.

### FR3.6 – View System Statistics (Analytics API)
Admins shall access system-wide metrics such as:
- Number of active users  
- Total workouts  
- Weekly activity  
Returned using analytics API endpoints.

### FR3.7 – Access System Logs (API)
Admins shall retrieve system logs (errors, events) via secured JSON API routes.

### FR3.8 – Support External Integrations
The system shall support admin-generated API keys/tokens for integration with third-party services.


